[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Java Helpers**\n\nI'm considering the existing Java helper for class tags. Adding a dedicated Java helper just for population might be acceptable, but I wonder about the implications. There’s the question of whether it’s necessary to create a one-to-one dynamic access coverage test class file. I'm trying to weigh the benefits of simplifying things against potential complexity it could introduce. It’s really about finding that right balance, isn't it?\n\n**Clarifying implementation order**\n\nI'm noting that `compileTestJava` occurs before Scala, so that shouldn't be an issue. I wonder if adding a Java helper is related, or if it's from an existing Java test. It’s worth considering implementing it anyway. I think using the existing `DeprecatedArrayClassTag` could be helpful. Just ensuring I’m on the right path with this implementation!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02ab03fe9132a203016a1047534c20819f8c0d57fe0c38fdd9\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEEdnS0Oaq0vuceS5IFCR8ojjL-QYwcwycwchvua5VcM18XGq7dRvNXMibNF3RU0R-o_VXSlJyE8y2AKZRWI_UqrUSb5OnzREQDsEtb7TnM-AfKlWSZF_I_Tcj7fL1qtjSzf4yb9jUHA-n_bZ7n_OqyHEB2q9w-XVoNCyOruHAkm-tawRghLSy8xwW-GLqQMsXXwJ92rOQt20ztwTI5UFgWhW-mH-zKGWqvcfqwrBnwnp4IHZpm6gatyUGvMzLV9NLnics_8SXrw2doVexq9J-d3n_GdQMAKUyDlX1qpBj8RI00TYuH6sV2QN8OnjrO10gHgXJIh3E-TIfkJmpHV04FatzK5KwolXrcgNU6Q_ZVoXE2cxkG0mVUc3KYBnIZjhP6zYmMvAgW6W9qhZt-K5Ox2yJaew2Q7C68-8tbMunYi9yUJ9WHYMnono_vzXFEKKEMh3EELjVFYIh-_FdzR1baHg2cLEpcwARcbAr0UjLNbLzq-5jmDLQ77IjtsVMu5NUroKfQTRwmcZT93OubviDwOfQM1UqjzSUt26YhCo8W9nxOGsNtM6HHQga-iLCJx5jFNq0z6GmsdwekN1uPm-Lwl1bnhnFDMT_PkFy0RIZChzxVXHwGvUJZWDqVei8qYb46y6QqKTBapyRegfddaqt0hR-VEn43fu3hKpjPpA0vDvOLIJ8iedZeH2Oe3bp_C-YmezSELOfcKbDvLh5FiT-Ofy47lLImHFG8yghQwYjCMhfMNn8nv6v6Ig9PjOpiOBDPh6uvnHw-124cH2TLEWbTokpPsep7Ovafdyr9PboD9QFINrDNlaUXZodgr0c6za8E1Rrma7HpFBzOhB_9Zup8CpTeiT7_bzCXRnDBr_kEFnQ-o5tr_mYnFN